pageContext.claim: “In the 2016 Election I was winning by so much in Florida that Broward County, which was very late with vote tabulation and probably getting ready to do a “number,” couldn't do it because not enough people live in Broward for them to falsify a victory!”
pageContext.analysis: Broward County was the center of the 2000 presidential election scandal. What the president is describing is more counting than "finding." It takes time to count all the votes including absentee ballots. There's no evidence of vote fabrication in the 2016 election.
